CatDescriptText: Carrie Evans, housewife and part-time worker, 1545 Centre Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 8, 1959, pg. B1 with question: "Do you believe the John James Racket Squad is driving the numbers racket out of Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "No, I don't think so. The squad is just making them shift from one spot to another, and then back again.  I think that they should be out getting 'sporting' women who keep this city from begin the wonderful city that it should be.  The police look at them, but there are no arrests.  Maybe they are being paid to turn away."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Carrie Evans wearing dark short sleeved dress with light colored notched collar, holding paper bag and standing in front of Jenkins Arcade with Thrift Drugs and Kappels in background, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
